@NODE "ReadCapacityPPC" "ReadCapacityPPC Usage:"

  @{FG SHINE} NAME @{FG TEXT}
      ReadCapacityPPC
      
  @{FG SHINE} DESCRIPTION @{FG TEXT}
      Read a drive's capacity using HD_SCSICMD, then display the number of
      sectors & sector size on stdout.  The reason ReadCapacityPPC does not
      compute the actual size of the drive is because there are a lot of
      large disk drives available these days, which easily overflow 32-bit
      arithmetic.  32-bits can only represent numbers up to 4294967295 or
      around 4 GBbytes.  A good calculator should have no problem multiplying
      the results together to give you the Hard Disk's capacity.  Or you
      can re-write the code to use floating-point mathematics, just send @{" me " LINK "Author"}
      a copy of the modified source code!

  @{FG SHINE} COPYRIGHT @{FG TEXT}
      Copyright (C) 1990 by Ralph Babel, Falkenweg 3, D-6204 Taunusstein, FRG
      all rights reserved - alle Rechte vorbehalten

  @{FG SHINE} SYNOPSIS @{FG TEXT}

      ReadCapacity deviceName unitNumber
      
  @{FG SHINE} EXAMPLE @{FG TEXT}
      > ReadCapacityPPC scsi.device    4 >RAM:ScsiDev4.output
      > ReadCapacityPPC gvpscsi.device 6
      > ReadCapacityPPC a1ide.device   2 >RAM:Dev2.output 

  @{FG SHINE} HISTORY @{FG TEXT}
      16-Nov-2004 - Ported to AmigaOS4 & gcc (JTS).
      31-Oct-1995 - Modified to use stdio & to accept user TID as argv[1] (JTS).
      02-Jun-1990 - created

  @{FG SHINE} SEE ALSO @{FG TEXT}
      @{" Read Source Code " SYSTEM "Sys:Utilities/Multiview ReadCapacity.c"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ReadHardBlocksPPC" "ReadHardBlocksPPC Usage:"

  @{FG SHINE} NAME @{FG TEXT}
      ReadHardBlocksPPC

  @{FG SHINE} DESCRIPTION @{FG TEXT}
     Read a HardDisk attached to the given deviceName in order to get information
     on the RDB, PART & LSEG blocks, located in the first 16 blocks
     of every HardDisk on the SCSI bus.  On the AmigaOne RDB_LOCATION_LIMIT
     is no longer large enough due to the number of BOOT blocks in front
     of the Partition blocks.
 
  @{FG SHINE} SYNOPSIS @{FG TEXT}
      ReadHardBlocks deviceName unitNumber [>outputText]

  @{FG SHINE} EXAMPLE @{FG TEXT}
      > ReadHardBlocksPPC scsi.device    4 >RAM:ScsiDev4.output
      > ReadHardBlocksPPC gvpscsi.device 6
      > ReadHardBlocksPPC a1ide.device   2 >RAM:Dev2.output 

  @{FG SHINE} COPYRIGHT @{FG TEXT}
     Copyright (C) 1995-2004 by J.T. Steichen, All rights reserved.
     
  @{FG SHINE} HISTORY @{FG TEXT}
      16-Nov-2004 - Ported to AmigaOS4 & gcc.
      31-Oct-1995 - Created.

  @{FG SHINE} AUTHOR @{FG TEXT}
     @{" That's me! " LINK "Author"}

  @{FG SHINE} SEE ALSO @{FG TEXT}
      @{" ReadHardBlocksPPC   " LINK "ReadHardBlocksPPC"}
      @{" Read Source Code    " SYSTEM "Sys:Utilities/Multiview RDBInformer.c"}
      @{" Read Example Output " SYSTEM "Sys:Utilities/Multiview RDBInformer.output"}

@ENDNODE

